#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np14"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:0.4"
msgid "Kosiyavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:0.5"
msgid "14. Chabbassasikkhāpada"
msgstr "14. The training rule on six years"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-np14.1, pts-vp-en2.79, ms1V_2135
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū anuvassaṃ santhataṃ kārāpenti."
msgstr "At that time monks were getting blankets made every year."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.3"
msgid "Te yācanabahulā viññattibahulā viharanti—"
msgstr "They kept on begging and asking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.4"
msgid "“eḷakalomāni detha."
msgstr "“Give wool;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.5"
msgid "Eḷakalomehi attho”ti."
msgstr "we need wool.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.6"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.7"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā anuvassaṃ santhataṃ kārāpessanti, yācanabahulā viññattibahulā viharissanti—"
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics get blankets made every year, begging and asking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.8"
msgid "‘eḷakalomāni detha, eḷakalomehi attho’ti."
msgstr "‘Give wool; we need wool’?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.9"
msgid "Amhākaṃ pana sakiṃ katāni santhatāni pañcapi chapi vassāni honti, yesaṃ no dārakā uhadantipi ummihantipi undūrehipi khajjanti."
msgstr "We only make blankets for ourselves every five or six years, even though our children defecate and urinate on them and they are eaten by rats.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.10"
msgid "Ime pana samaṇā sakyaputtiyā anuvassaṃ santhataṃ kārāpenti, yācanabahulā viññattibahulā viharanti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.11"
msgid "‘eḷakalomāni detha, eḷakalomehi attho’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_2136
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.12"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.13"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.14"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.15"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū anuvassaṃ santhataṃ kārāpessanti, yācanabahulā viññattibahulā viharissanti—"
msgstr "“How can those monks act like this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.16"
msgid "‘eḷakalomāni detha, eḷakalomehi attho’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, pts-vp-pli3.228, ms1V_2137
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.17"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū te anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.18"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū anuvassaṃ santhataṃ kārāpenti, yācanabahulā viññattibahulā viharanti—"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that some monks are acting like this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.19"
msgid "‘eḷakalomāni detha, eḷakalomehi attho’”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.20"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.21"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.22"
msgid "kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā anuvassaṃ santhataṃ kārāpessanti, yācanabahulā viññattibahulā viharissanti—"
msgstr "How can those foolish men get blankets made every year, begging and asking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.23"
msgid "‘eḷakalomāni detha, eḷakalomehi attho’ti."
msgstr "‘Give wool; we need wool’?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.24"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.25"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.25a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc4, ms1V_2138, pts-vp-en2.80
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.26"
msgid "“Navaṃ pana bhikkhunā santhataṃ kārāpetvā chabbassāni dhāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk gets a new blanket made, he should keep it for six years."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.27"
msgid "Orena ce channaṃ vassānaṃ taṃ santhataṃ vissajjetvā vā avissajjetvā vā aññaṃ navaṃ santhataṃ kārāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "Whether that blanket has been given away or not, if he gets another new blanket made in less than six years, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-en2.4, ms1V_2139
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:1.28"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc6, pts-cs-bu-np14.2, ms1V_2140
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu kosambiyaṃ gilāno hoti."
msgstr "At one time a certain monk in Kosambī was ill."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.2"
msgid "Ñātakā tassa bhikkhuno santike dūtaṃ pāhesuṃ—"
msgstr "His relatives sent him a message:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.3"
msgid "“āgacchatu bhadanto mayaṃ upaṭṭhahissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Venerable, we’ll attend on you.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.4"
msgid "Bhikkhūpi evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Other monks"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.5"
msgid "“gacchāvuso, ñātakā taṃ upaṭṭhahissantī”ti."
msgstr "urged him to go,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.6"
msgid "So evamāha—"
msgstr "but he said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.7"
msgid "“bhagavatā, āvuso, sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ—"
msgstr "“The Master has laid down a training rule"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.8"
msgid "‘navaṃ pana bhikkhunā santhataṃ kārāpetvā chabbassāni dhāretabban’ti."
msgstr "that a monk who gets a new blanket made must keep it for six years."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.9"
msgid "Ahañcamhi gilāno, na sakkomi santhataṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "Because I’m sick, I’m not able to take my blanket when I travel."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.10"
msgid "Mayhañca vinā santhatā na phāsu hoti."
msgstr "And because I’m not comfortable without it,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.11"
msgid "Nāhaṃ gamissāmī”ti."
msgstr "I cannot go.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: ms1V_2141
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.12"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.13"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.14"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānassa bhikkhuno santhatasammutiṃ dātuṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to give a blanket-permission to a sick monk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.15"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā."
msgstr "And it should be given in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.16"
msgid "Tena gilānena bhikkhunā saṃghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "After approaching the Order, the sick monk should put his upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior monks. He should then squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.17"
msgid "‘ahaṃ, bhante, gilāno"
msgstr "‘Venerables, I’m sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.18"
msgid "na sakkomi santhataṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "I’m not able to take my blanket when I travel."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.19"
msgid "Sohaṃ, bhante, saṃghaṃ santhatasammutiṃ yācāmī’ti."
msgstr "I ask the Order for a blanket-permission.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.20"
msgid "Dutiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "And he should ask a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.21"
msgid "Tatiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "and a third time."

#. REF: ms1V_2142
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.22"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "A competent and capable monk should then inform the Order:"

#. HTML: </p><div class="kamma"><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.23"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.81
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.24"
msgid "Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu gilāno na sakkoti santhataṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "This monk so-and-so is sick. He is not able to take his blanket when he travels."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.25"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ santhatasammutiṃ yācati."
msgstr "He is asking the Order for a blanket-permission."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.26"
msgid "Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno santhatasammutiṃ dadeyya."
msgstr "If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should give a blanket-permission to monk so-and-so."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.27"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9, pts-vp-pli3.229, ms1V_2143
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.28"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.29"
msgid "Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu gilāno na sakkoti santhataṃ ādāya pakkamituṃ."
msgstr "This monk so-and-so is sick. He is not able to take his blanket when he travels."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.30"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ santhatasammutiṃ yācati."
msgstr "He is asking the Order for a blanket-permission."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.31"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno santhatasammutiṃ deti."
msgstr "The Order gives a blanket-permission to monk so-and-so."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.32"
msgid "Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno santhatasammutiyā dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr "Any monk who approves of giving a blanket-permission to monk so-and-so should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.33"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should speak up."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_2144
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.34"
msgid "Dinnā saṃghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno santhatasammuti."
msgstr "The Order has given a blanket-permission to monk so-and-so."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.35"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.36"
msgid "Kevametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.’"

#. HTML: </p></div><p>
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_2145
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.37"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.37a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_2146
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.38"
msgid "“Navaṃ pana bhikkhunā santhataṃ kārāpetvā chabbassāni dhāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "‘If a monk gets a new blanket made, he should keep it for six years."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:2.39"
msgid "Orena ce channaṃ vassānaṃ taṃ santhataṃ vissajjetvā vā avissajjetvā vā aññaṃ navaṃ santhataṃ kārāpeyya, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "Whether that blanket has been given away or not, if he gets another new blanket made in less than six years, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, pts-cs-bu-np14.3, ms1V_2147
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.1"
msgid "Navaṃ nāma"
msgstr "New:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.2"
msgid "karaṇaṃ upādāya vuccati."
msgstr "newly made is what is meant."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_2148
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.3"
msgid "Santhataṃ nāma"
msgstr "A blanket:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.4"
msgid "santharitvā kataṃ hoti avāyimaṃ."
msgstr "it is made by spreading out, not by weaving."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc15, ms1V_2149
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.5"
msgid "Kārāpetvāti"
msgstr "Gets made:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.6"
msgid "karitvā vā kārāpetvā vā."
msgstr "makes or gets made."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc16, ms1V_2150
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.7"
msgid "Chabbassāni dhāretabbanti"
msgstr "He should keep it for six years:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.8"
msgid "chabbassaparamatā dhāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "he should keep it for a minimum of six years."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc17, ms1V_2151
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.9"
msgid "Orena ce channaṃ vassānanti"
msgstr "In less than six years:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.10"
msgid "ūnakachabbassāni."
msgstr "fewer than six years."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc18, ms1V_2152
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.11"
msgid "Taṃ santhataṃ vissajjetvāti"
msgstr "That blanket has been given away:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.12"
msgid "aññesaṃ datvā."
msgstr "it has been given to others."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc19, ms1V_2153
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.13"
msgid "Avissajjetvāti"
msgstr "Not:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.14"
msgid "na kassaci datvā."
msgstr "it has not been given to anyone."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc20, ms1V_2154
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.15"
msgid "Aññatra bhikkhusammutiyāti"
msgstr "except if the monks have agreed:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.16"
msgid "ṭhapetvā bhikkhusammutiṃ aññaṃ navaṃ santhataṃ karoti vā kārāpeti vā, payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr "for the act of making another new blanket, or getting one made, unless he has the permission of the monks, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.17"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the blanket, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.18"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The blanket should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.19"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. HTML: <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.20"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in [Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17](pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13), with appropriate substitutions. "

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.21"
msgid "“idaṃ me, bhante, santhataṃ ūnakachabbassāni kārāpitaṃ, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this blanket which I got made after less than six years without the permission of the monks is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.22"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.23"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.82
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.24"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.25"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this blanket back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.25a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc21, ms1V_2155
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.26"
msgid "Attanā vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he finishes what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.27"
msgid "Attanā vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he gets others to finish what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.28"
msgid "Parehi vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he finishes himself what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.29"
msgid "Parehi vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he gets others to finish what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.29a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc22, ms1V_2156
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.30"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.31"
msgid "chabbassāni karoti,"
msgstr "if he makes one after six years;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.32"
msgid "atirekachabbassāni karoti,"
msgstr "if he makes one after more than six years;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.33"
msgid "aññassatthāya karoti vā kārāpeti vā,"
msgstr "if he makes one, or gets one made, for the sake of another;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.34"
msgid "aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā paribhuñjati,"
msgstr "if he obtains what was made by another and then uses it;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.35"
msgid "vitānaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā sāṇipākāraṃ vā bhisiṃ vā bibbohanaṃ vā karoti,"
msgstr "if he makes a canopy, a floor cover, a screen-wall, a mattress, or a pillow;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.36"
msgid "bhikkhusammutiyā,"
msgstr "if he has the permission of the monks;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.37"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.38"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc23, ms1V_2157
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np14:3.39"
msgid "Chabbassasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr "The fourth rule, the training rule on six years, is finished."
